Persian Gulf Stocks: Global, Masraf Al Rayan, Wataniya Telecom

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-09-21T12:18:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/persian-gulf-stocks-qatar-telecom-and-wataniya-telecom.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  rose the
most this month, gaining 0.5 percent at the 2 p.m. close in the
emirate. Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM)  advanced 0.6 percent.  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX
General Index (ADSMI)  was little changed.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Global Investment House KSCC (GLOBAL)   dropped 6 percent,
the most in a month, to 39.5 fils.  National Bank of Umm Al
Qaiwain (NBQ)  said a Dubai court will look into its appeal in a
dispute with the Kuwait-based investment bank. National Bank
shares didn’t trade today.  Masraf Al Rayan (MARK)   rallied to the highest in more
than five years, gaining 0.9 percent to 24.98 riyals. Qatar’s
second-largest Shariah-compliant lender had the outlook on its
A3 long-term issuer rating changed to positive from stable at
Moody’s Investors Service.  National Mobile Telecommunications Co. (NMTC KK) rose for
the first time since Sept. 7, gaining 1 percent to 1,980 fils.
The Kuwaiti phone company known as Wataniya Telecom had its
price estimate raised to 2.6 dinars from 2.35 dinars at  HSBC
Holdings Plc. (HSBA)   Qatar Telecom QSC (QTEL QD) advanced the most in more than
a month, jumping 1.5 percent to 150.5 riyals. The Persian Gulf
country’s biggest company by revenue will pay interest to note
holders on Oct. 14 and Oct. 19. Separately, HSBC raised the
company’s price estimate 5.4 percent to 180 riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  